{"lemma":"بَيُّوتِ","slug":"بَيُّوتِ","root":"ب.#.ت","root_slug":"ب-_-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-_-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3607"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8F%D9%91%D9%88%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of بَيْت (bayt)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/bu.juːt/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3607","headword_ar":"بَيُّوتٌ","root":"byt","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That has remained throughout a night"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and so become stale; stale from being a night old"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAy^itN","text_ar":"بَايِتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": both, in this sense, [but the latter more usually,] applied to bread. (S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool,"},{"kind":"text","text":"water, (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has become so from its having remained throughout a night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that remains during the night beneath the sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 553:) or water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has been cooled in the leathern bag by night;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, milk; for [Az says,] I heard an Arab of the desert say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisoqiniY mino bay~uwti Als~iqaA='i","text_ar":"اِسْقِنِى مِنْ بَيُّوتِ السِّقَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give thou me to drink of the milk that has been milked at night and left in the skin so that it has become cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool, by night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) In the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faSab~aHato HawDa qirFY bay~uwtaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"the meaning seems to be,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiraY HawoDK bay~uwtaA","text_ar":"قِرَى حَوْضٍ بَيُّوتَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they"},{"kind":"text","text":"(app. camels)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came in the morning to"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the collected water of a trough, which"},{"kind":"text","text":"water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had remained throughout the night and so become cold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the phrase being inverted. (M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN bay~uwtN","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ بَيُّوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, for which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of which, one passes the night in anxiety"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ham~N bay~uwtN","text_ar":"هَمٌّ بَيُّوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anxiety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grief, that has remained during the night in the bosom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sin~N bay~uwtapN","text_ar":"سِنٌّ بَيُّوتَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tooth that does not fall out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become shed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}